From: Paul Argoud <paul@argoud.net>
Subject: [PATCH] Add mxchat_pre_vector_query short-circuit filter

Lets companion plugins (DuckDB / MotherDuck / Qdrant adapters, etc.)
bypass the Pinecone HTTP call in find_relevant_content_pinecone() with
native PHP. Returns a Pinecone-shaped response array; null falls
through to the existing behaviour.

Follows the WordPress core `pre_*` short-circuit convention — same
pattern used by pre_get_posts, pre_user_query, pre_option_*: return
null for the default flow, return a value to skip the rest of the
function.

Total change: ~14 lines added (filter call + if/else wrapper).
Existing wp_remote_post block stays untouched, just moved into the
`else` branch. All downstream logic (chunk reassembly, role checks,
similarity analysis, RAG context assembly) is reused as-is.

Applies cleanly against mxchat-basic 3.2.6.

Signed-off-by: Paul Argoud <paul@argoud.net>
---
--- a/includes/class-mxchat-integrator.php
+++ b/includes/class-mxchat-integrator.php
@@ -5443,11 +5443,27 @@
     if (!empty($namespace)) {
         $request_body['namespace'] = $namespace;
     }
-    
+
+    // ───────────────── BEGIN PATCH ─────────────────
+    // Let companion plugins short-circuit the Pinecone HTTP call.
+    // Returning a Pinecone-shaped array bypasses the network entirely;
+    // returning null falls through to the existing wp_remote_post() flow.
+    $pre = apply_filters('mxchat_pre_vector_query', null, array(
+        'vector'    => $user_embedding,
+        'top_k'     => $request_body['topK'],
+        'namespace' => $namespace,
+        'bot_id'    => $bot_id,
+    ));
+
+    if (is_array($pre) && isset($pre['matches'])) {
+        $results = $pre;
+    } else {
+    // ───────────────── END PATCH (top) ─────────────
+
     //error_log("MXCHAT DEBUG: About to call Pinecone API");
     //error_log("  - Endpoint: " . $api_endpoint);
     //error_log("  - Namespace in request: " . (!empty($namespace) ? $namespace : 'NOT SET'));
-    
+
     $response = wp_remote_post($api_endpoint, array(
         'headers' => array(
             'Api-Key' => $api_key,
@@ -5489,7 +5505,11 @@
         $this->current_valid_urls = [];
         return '';
     }
-    
+
+    // ───────────────── BEGIN PATCH (bottom) ────────
+    } // end else { ... wp_remote_post fallback }
+    // ───────────────── END PATCH ───────────────────
+
     //error_log("MXCHAT DEBUG: Pinecone response structure:");
     //error_log("  - Has 'matches' key: " . (isset($results['matches']) ? 'yes' : 'no'));
     //error_log("  - Has 'namespace' key: " . (isset($results['namespace']) ? 'yes (' . $results['namespace'] . ')' : 'no'));
